<body>
	<h1>Declare Wages</h1>

	As a client I want to enter my wages for the week in which I earned them so that I can ensure my benefit is accurate

	<div class="Acceptance Criteria">
		<h3>Acceptance Criteria</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>No more then 10 employers may be entered in any one declaration</li>
			<li>No more then 120 hours total may be entered in any one declaration</li>
			<li>No more than 5,000 dollars in total may be entered in any one declaration</li>
			<li>No more than 59 minutes can be added into a minutes field</li>
			<li>The client can cancel a wage entry that was added in error while declaring wages</li>
			<li>The client will select the week of change first</li>
			<li>The client can select a previously-entered (in MyMSD) employer or add a new employer</li>
			<li>The client may choose 1 of 4 options for entering wages:</li>
			<ol>
				<li>Total gross and total hours for the week</li>
				<li>Hourly gross and total hours for the week</li>
				<li>Hourly gross and hours by day for the week</li>
				<li>No wages this week</li>
			</ol>
			<li>The client may only declare from the week of their previous declaration (or the week of their grant date), whichever is later.  </li>
			<li>Where a client attempts to declares income before their benefit is current, they will be directed to contact us.  </li>
			<li>The client may not declare a future weeks wages.  </li>
			<li>Clients on a sole parent rate of benefit will have the option of entering unsubsidized childcare cost</li>
		</ul>
	</div>

